quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  14,43,(they will be) running with their heads raised without blinking their eyes and their hearts (will be) vacant
  14,44,"And warn mankind of the day when the punishment will come upon them, then those who were unjust would say, “Our Fosterer ! give us time till a near term, we will respond to your invitation and we will follow the messengers.” (They will be answered), “Did you not swear before, that there will be no decline for you"
  14,45,And you dwelt in the dwellings of those who were unjust to themselves and it was made clear to you how We dealt with them and We had set forth similitude’s for you.”
  14,46,"And they had planned their plan, and their plan is with Allah, and if their plan was implemented (it would have been sufficient) for moving away mountains thereby"
  14,47,"So do not think that Allah will go against His promise to His messengers, Allah is certainly Mighty, Capable of retribution"
  14,48,"The day on which the earth will be changed to other than the (present) earth and the skies (too), and they will appear before Allah, the One, the Omnipotent"
  14,49,And on that day you will see the criminals linked together in chains
  14,50,their shirts made of pitch and the fire covering their faces
  14,51,that Allah may reward every soul (according to) that which it earned. Allah is certainly Quick (at settling) the account
  14,52,"This is a message for mankind that they may be warned thereby and that they may know that He is certainly one God, and that men of understanding may be mindful"